---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  description="Official rules and guidelines for participation rewards during the testing phase of our project. Learn how you can earn rewards for contributing to the development and improvement of our platform."
  title="Participation Rewards Rules Â· Aaron Network"
>
  <section class="py-8 px-4 mx-auto max-w-7xl">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-6">Participation Rewards Rules</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-center mb-12 text-gray-600">
      These rules outline how participants in our project testing phase can earn rewards for their contributions. Please read carefully to understand the process, criteria, and distribution of rewards.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <!-- Section 1: Eligibility -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">1. Eligibility</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          To be eligible for participation rewards, you must meet the following criteria:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-4 text-gray-700">
          <li>Testing Telegram bot and address rating calculation functionality</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 2: Reward Structure -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">2. Reward Structure</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Rewards are distributed based on the quality and quantity of contributions during the testing period.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-4 text-gray-700">
          <li><strong>Bug Reporting:</strong> Each verified bug report earns you tokens.</li>
          <li><strong>Feature Suggestions:</strong> Are eligible for rewards.</li>
          <li><strong>Feedback:</strong> Valuable feedback on usability, design, and functionality is appreciated and rewarded.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 3: How to Participate -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">3. How to Participate</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          To join the testing phase and be eligible for rewards, follow these steps:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-decimal list-inside mt-4 text-gray-700">
          <li>Use our telegram bot: <a href="https://t.me/CosmosReputationBot" target="_blank">@CosmosReputationBot</a>. </li>
          <li>Find errors in the bot and address rating calculation system.</li>
          <li>Send us messages about usage and errors by email or in the bot feedback.</li>
          <li>Link your cosmos address to our telegram bot.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 4: Distribution of Rewards -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">4. Distribution of Rewards</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Rewards will be paid automatically after the network launch. No further action is required. All participants who meet the requirements will receive their rewards in the form of tokens.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">
          Please make sure your address is correct to avoid delays in reward distribution.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 5: Terms and Conditions -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">5. Terms and Conditions</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          By participating in the testing phase, you agree to the following terms:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-4 text-gray-700">
          <li>All participants must comply our Terms of Service</li>
          <li>We reserve the right to disqualify participants who violate rules or engage in fraudulent activities.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 6: Contact Information -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">6. Contact Information</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          If you have any questions or need assistance regarding the participation rewards, please contact our support team at aaronetwork@proton.me
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
